         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3865" xml:lang="de">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <dateline>Cor. Morris Ave &amp; 155<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> Str. New York</dateline>
            <opener>Geehrter Herr!</opener>
            <p>Dr. <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Alfred Mercier</persName>
               <note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Dr. <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Alfred Mercier</persName> (1816-1894), a native Louisianan physician and writer. He was concerned with the promotion of <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.230">French and creole language</ref> and culture in <placeName ref="[authorityLink]">Louisiana</placeName>. For that purpose he co-founded <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.3465">
                     <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">L’Athénée Louisianais</hi>
                  </ref> in 1875. His later literary and philologist works implement and discuss the <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.languages#L.349">creole language of Louisiana</ref> (Jumonville 2002, cf. <bibl>
                     <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.2325">Krämer 2013</ref>
                  </bibl>).</note> aus New Orleans theilte mir kürzlich mit, daß Sie beabsichtigen eine Schrift über die Kreolen zu veröffentlichen. Haben Sie doch die Güte mir 1 Exemplar derselben unter <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">starkem </hi>+Band zuzusenden, sobald sie erschienen ist, da ich sie gern verwenden möchte.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Ergebenst</salute>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Karl Knortz</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
            <dateline>Prof. Hugo Schuchardt<lb/>Graetz<lb/>Austria</dateline>
         </div>
